info.title: Resource Pool Management API
info.description: Resource Pool Management API### Based on TMF API Reference : TMF API Reference TMF TMF685 - Resource Pool Management API ###

parameters.name: fields
parameters.description: list of fields returned in response

ApplicableTimePeriod.title: ApplicableTimePeriod

daysOfWeek.description: A day or days representing when the schedule is applicable.

ApplicableTimePeriod.description: The period of time for which Capacity or CapacityDemand applies.

Capacity.title: Capacity
Capacity.description: Specific ability of an entity measured in quantity and units of quantity over an extended period.

id.description: Unique identifier of the capacity object.

type.description: Indicates the referred capacity object type.

baseType.description: Indicates the referred capacity object base type.

id.description: Unique error ID, used for logging purposes, UUID format

code.description: A string coding the error type. This is given to caller so he can translate them if required.

message.description: A short localized string that describes the error.

retryable.description: A boolean that provides info is request retryable

severity.description:
"Describes severity of error. Order from most to least critical is: FATAL, ERROR, WARN, INFO, DEBUG, TRACE
* `FATAL` Designates very severe error events that will presumably lead the application to abort.
* `ERROR` Designates error events that might still allow the application to continue running.
* `WARN` Designates potentially harmful situations.
* `INFO` Designates informational messages that highlight the progress of the application at coarse-grained level.
* `DEBUG` Designates fine-grained informational events that are most useful to debug an application.
* `TRACE` Designates finer-grained informational events than the DEBUG. "

ProductOfferingConfigRef.title: ProductOfferingConfigRef

id.description: Unique identifier

group.description:
"Used to categorize product offerings by hierarchy (horizontal grouping)
* `service` service
* `addon` addon
* `discount` discount
* `device` device
* `SIM` SIM
* `VAS` external partner offering
* `bundle` bundle
* `bundledProduct` bundled product
* `tariff` tariff
* `number` number
* `topup` topup
* `deliveryMethod` delivery method
* `billDelivery` bill delivery "

characteristics.description: A list of configurable product Offering characteristics

productOfferingPrices.description: A list of configurable product Offering prices

ProductOfferingConfigRef.description: Selected Product Offering with configurable characteristics

ProductOfferingPriceConfigRef.title: ProductOfferingPriceConfigRef

id.description: Unique identifier

characteristics.description: A list of configurable price characteristics

ProductOfferingPriceConfigRef.description: Selected Product Offering Price with configurable characteristics

QuantityType.title: QuantityType

units.description: Units the quantity is measured in

QuantityType.description: Representation of a quantity of something. I can also be used to represent a quantity range

id.description: Unique identifier

RelatedPartyRef.title: RelatedPartyRef

id.description: Unique identifier

RelatedPartyRef.description: RelatedParty reference. A related party defines party or party role linked to a specific entity.

id.description: A string. Identifier of an instance of the Reservation.

href.description: A string. Hyperlink to access the reservation.

description.description: A string. free-text description of the reservation.

reservationState.description: A string. The life cycle state of the reservation. It can be 'In progress', 'Completed', 'Rejected' and 'Cancelled'.

ReservationItem.title: ReservationItem

id.description: A string. Identifier of an instance of the ReservationItem.

type.description: Resource pool type. E.g. mobileMSISDN or mobileDevice.

reservationItemState.description: A string. The life cycle state of the each reservation item.

appliedCapacities.description: The amount of capacity that is applied or applicable to be consumed.

ReservationItem.description: An identified part of the reservation. A reservation is decomposed into one or more reservation items.

ResourcePool.title: ResourcePool

id.description: A string. Identifier of an instance of the Resource Pool.

href.description: A string. Hyperlink to access the Resource Pool.

description.description: A string. free-text description of the Resource Pool.

type.description: Resource pool type. E.g. mobileMSISDN or mobileDevice.

capacities.description: Specific ability of an entity measured in quantity and units of quantity over an extended period.

ResourcePool.description: ResourcePool manages resource capacity with the resource state

entityReferredType.description: The actual type of the target instance when needed for disambiguation.

VersionReference.title: VersionReference

id.description: Unique identifier of the Reference

VersionReference.description: Generic link to another versioning resource

accessToken.description: Access token in JWT or opaque format sent in HTTP Authorization header, Bearer schema
accessToken.name: Authorization

apiKey.description: API key for technical accounts (opaque format) sent in HTTP Authorization header, no schema
apiKey.name: Authorization
